{
  "content": "An Essay exploring the difference between tasking and delegating, and why it matters, concluding: Delegate to teams; task within them."
}

{
  "content": "An essay discussing when to task and when to delegate."
}

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Entrust",
        "Bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "text": "(verb): ",
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": "Assign the responsibility for doing something to (someone)"
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "The notion of team entails shared accountability: good or bad, the outcomes should be attributed to the entire team rather than to any individual.",
        "Italic": true
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Task",
        "Bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": " ("
      },
      {
        "text": "verb)",
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": ": Assign a piece of work to."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Delegate ",
        "Bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": "(verb)",
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": ": Entrust ... to another person, typically one who is less senior than oneself."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "H1",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Task vs Delegate"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "TLDR; Delegate to teams; task within them."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "I find that people often use the terms task and delegate interchangeably. This can lead to team failure both from inside and outside the team. I now try to understand which term should be used to ensure we are not damaging the team."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "H2",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Let's Get Pedantic"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "To start off let us just look at the definitions."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "So one cannot delegate inside of the team. We can allocate parts of the work to different members of the team but we all own its success."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "\nWhen there is delegation inside of a team it breaks the collective accountability and starts finger-pointing, and that is ... bad."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "\nOn the flip side if you ask a team to do something without ownership then the team is not complete. Back to the Agile Alliance:"
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "If there is any huddle to the task, they cannot move forward, they have to stop and throw the issue over the fence to the tasker.  "
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "H2",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Phrasing"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": " One can often hear the difference in the language used."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "\n\"We will fix it by Friday.\""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "\"We don't understand the problem we need to dive deeper. \""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "\"That's out of the scope of our mission.\""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "\"We will figure that out.\""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "These are all delegating phrases. With each one, the "
      },
      {
        "text": "we ",
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": "in each phrase is accepting responsibility for completion or discussing what their responsibility is."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "I will explore how to solve this?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Let me play with that for a while."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "I can test that out."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "I will work on that today."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "If you have that done today I can start on this tomorrow."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "These are all tasking phrases the "
      },
      {
        "text": "I",
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": " in each phrase is signaling, informing the team about their action, not committing, not accepting ownership but informing so the team can move forward as one."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "H2",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Finishing up"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "AlignLeft",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "In the end, this clarification between tasking work and delegating responsibility ensures our teams have things they can achieve and ensures they work together to achieve it.  "
      },
      {
        "text": "Delegate to teams; task within them. ",
        "Bold": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "H2",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "One more thing"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "It is much easier to delegate problems, this is because it is a clear way to ensure you are giving ownership. Please solve this problem."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "One can view delegating as a process of defining the problem that needs to be solved, where tasking is the process of building the solution."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "This gets to the heart of it for me.  "
      },
      {
        "text": "One tasks work; one delegates ownership",
        "Bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": ". Ok, Erik thanks for making me read a dictionary, but why should I care?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "H2",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Tasking, Delegating, and Teams"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "When we see high functioning teams, whether that is a SEAL Team, an executive team, a sports team, or a project team, responsibility is shared.  The agile alliance sums it up well with:"
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "The team is expected to possess all of the necessary competencies, whether technical (programming, designing, testing) or business (domain knowledge, ",
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": "decision making ability",
        "Italic": true,
        "Bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": ").",
        "Italic": true
      }
    ]
  }
]
